+## Summary
+
+- **CVE-2026-3449** describes a promise hang when an `AbortSignal` passed to `once()` is aborted
+- **@tootallnate/once@1.1.2 does not implement `AbortSignal`** — it uses a `.cancel()` API instead
+- The vulnerable code path **cannot be triggered** on 1.1.2
+- Scanner alerts mapping this CVE to 1.1.2 are a **false positive** under accurate, version-specific analysis
+- **No remediation patch is required** for @tootallnate/once@1.1.2
+- This entry is a **dummy patch** documenting the above for Root republish
